FBIS3-56039 "drsov009_b_94012" FBIS-SOV-94-009 Document Type:Daily Report 13 Jan 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Political Issues Yeltsin Allows 15 Jan Journalists' Ball in Kremlin PM1201133194 Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA in Russian 12 Jan 94 p 1 PM1201133194 Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA Language: Russian Article Type:BFN ["Own Information", ITAR-TASS report under the "Yesterday" rubric: "President Personally Upheld Journalists' Interests"] [Text] Russian Federation President Boris Yeltsin has given orders that the State Kremlin Palace be made available for the traditional journalists' ball 15 January, at which the annual awards ceremony of the Union of Journalists of Russia will take place. As has already been reported, the previous day the journalists were denied the opportunity to hold the ball in this building as it it an "official facility." It took a personal intervention by the head of state for the journalists' request to be granted.
